Adapter for DatabasesRecycler

Constructor:
* databases - property that holds a List of Database instances that are used to build a list by DatabasesRecycler
* presenter - DatabasesPresenter
* view - DatabaseFragment

* onCreateViewHolder - inflates fragment_database.xml file and returns inflated view

* onBindViewHolder(viewHolder: ViewHolder, i: Int) - configures viewHolder:
	* sets lockImg icon according to isOpen property of Database instance from
	  databases property
	* sets databaseName to name property of Database instance
	* sets onClickListener on 3 dots menu:

	Creates popup menu inflating database_item_menu.xml
	Sets onMenuItemClickListener to respond to clicks on menu items
	* if database.isOpen is false disable `Close` and `Edit` items using
	item.setEnabled(false)

Popup menu onMenuItemClick:
Export:
0. get `i` using getAdapterPosition()
1. calls view.showExportDialog(name)
name - name of the database retrieved from `databases` property by index `i`
2. saves database index `i` to presenter.exportIndex

Delete:
0. obtains `name` of the database to delete using getAdapterPosition()
1. view.confirmDelete(name) - show dialog to confirm deletion of database

Edit:
navigate to EditDatabaseFragment passing through Database instance

Close:
calls presenter.closeDatabase(i) where `i` is database index

* getItemCount - returns size of databases property

* removeItem(name) - removes database by specified name
0. searches for database by its name in `databases` property
1. removes database from `databases` property
2. notifyItemRemoved(index: Int)
3. notifyItemRangeRemoved(startPosition: Int, itemCount: Int)
